_:N84f6bb539cc24cd38fa402717676c6ce <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://schema.org/BreadcrumbList> <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
_:N6b3bcb1c53944518ad0421f5b682ca60 <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"qualified-lawyer-opportunities\">Qualified lawyer opportunities</h2>\n\n<p>Departments (particularly the Government Legal Department) fill vacancies when gaps in their legal capacity cannot be addressed by existing staff.</p>\n\n<p>Qualified lawyer posts are open to barristers, solicitors and chartered legal executives who meet the professional qualifications criteria.</p>\n\n<p>The level of entry is dependent on your level of experience and the role on offer. Details of this are included in a department’s job vacancy.</p>\n\n<p>This <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/lawyers-in-government\">short film</a> showcases the breadth of work government lawyers and legal trainees are involved in.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"civil-service-jobs-website\">Civil Service Jobs Website</h2>\n\n<p>Qualified lawyer vacancies across government are advertised on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/csr/index.cgi\">Civil Service Jobs Website</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The Civil Service is an <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-service/about/equality-and-diversity\">equal opportunities employer</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"mailing-list\">Mailing List</h2>\n\n<p>To receive automatic job alerts for legal opportunities across government, we would recommend registering on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/csr/index.cgi\">Civil Service Jobs Website</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"eligibility\">Eligibility</h2>\n\n<p>To be eligible to apply for a qualified lawyer post, you must ensure that you meet all the eligibility criteria stated in a department’s Vacancy Notice.  The four main areas are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>professional qualifications</li>\n  <li>academic qualifications</li>\n  <li>nationality requirements</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4 id=\"barristers\">Barristers</h4>\n\n<p>If you are a barrister, you must have successfully completed your 1 year pupillage or have been exempted from this by the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.barcouncil.org.uk/\">Bar Council.</a></p>\n\n<p>If you qualified outside England and Wales you will be required to complete the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.barstandardsboard.org.uk/qualifying-as-a-barrister/bar-training-requirements/transferring-lawyers/bar-transfer-test/\">Bar Transfer Test.</a></p>\n\n<h4 id=\"solicitors\">Solicitors</h4>\n\n<p>If you are a solicitor, you must have completed your training/QWE or have been exempted from this by the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.sra.org.uk/\">Solicitors Regulation Authority.</a></p>\n\n<p>If you qualified outside England and Wales, you may need to complete the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.sra.org.uk/become-solicitor/qualified-lawyers/\">Solicitors Qualifying Examination (SQE).</a></p>\n\n<h4 id=\"chartered-institute-of-legal-executives-cilex\">Chartered Institute of Legal Executives (<abbr title=\"Chartered Institute of Legal Executives\">CILEx</abbr>)</h4>\n\n<p>If you are a Fellow of <abbr title=\"Chartered Institute of Legal Executives\">CILEx</abbr> you will be eligible to apply if you either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>hold a qualifying law degree or</li>\n  <li>have completed the Graduate Diploma in Law or Common Professional Examination or</li>\n  <li>have passed exams (i.e. achieved 50% or above) in all seven of the foundation subjects in law taken at <abbr title=\"Chartered Institute of Legal Executives\">CILEx</abbr> Level 6</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The seven foundational topics of legal knowledge are:</p>\n\n<ol>\n  <li>Criminal Law</li>\n  <li>Equity and Trusts</li>\n  <li>Law of the European Union</li>\n  <li>Obligations 1 (Contract)</li>\n  <li>Obligations 2 (Tort)</li>\n  <li>Property/Land Law</li>\n  <li>Public Law (Constitutional Law, Administrative Law and Human Rights Law)</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h3 id=\"academic-qualifications\">Academic qualifications</h3>\n\n<p>All applicants will need to meet the following requirements:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you should have a minimum of a 2:1 degree in any subject</li>\n  <li>\n    <p>if you have a lower degree classification or do not hold a degree, some departments may consider your application. You must demonstrate equivalent high level academic and/or professional achievement</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>chartered legal executives should note that some departments are willing to consider applications from candidates who do not meet the minimum 2.1 degree criterion. You must have an overall average score of 65% across exams passed in the seven foundation subjects in law (where studied at <abbr title=\"Chartered Institute of Legal Executives\">CILEx</abbr> Level 6) to demonstrate the 2.1 degree equivalence.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3 id=\"nationality\">Nationality</h3>\n\n<p>You must meet all aspects of the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nationality-rules\">civil service nationality rules.</a></p>\n\n<p>Further information on the nationality requirements will be included in the job vacancies on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civilservicejobs.service.gov.uk/csr/index.cgi\">Civil Service Jobs Website.</a></p>\n\n<h2 id=\"flexible-careers\">Flexible careers</h2>\n\n<p>Lawyers work with their legal managers to develop their own career path. Lawyers are not expected to specialise in one area of law for their entire careers.</p>\n\n<p>Departments never assume that, because a lawyer has specialised in a particular field, they won’t have the capacity to take on a new challenge. Lawyers are encouraged to develop transferable skills which they can apply to the variety of legal work on offer.</p>\n\n<p>However, departments do recognise that, while some prefer variety, others prefer to establish a career in a particular field. Both choices can be accommodated.</p>\n\n<p>Legal teams’ primary duty is to provide their department with an effective service and make sure that their business needs continue to be met.</p>\n\n<p>Departments have clear policies surrounding the amount of time they expect their lawyers to remain in a particular post. This is usually between 3 and 4 years. After this time, lawyers considering a move are advised to work with their legal managers and consider what their next post might be.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"flexible-working\">Flexible working</h2>\n\n<p>Legal teams are willing to consider requests for flexible working. The most common flexible working arrangements include part-time working, flexible hours, home-working and job-sharing.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"salaries\">Salaries</h2>\n\n<p>Lawyers can expect to receive a fair and flexible pay and reward package.</p>\n\n<p>Individual departments have responsibility for their own pay and grading structure. Consequently, starting salaries for lawyers will vary according their department, location and experience.</p>\n\n<p>Information on the salary range is included in a department’s Vacancy Notice.</p>\n\n<p>However, you might expect:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Legal Officer - generally equivalent to 0 to 3 years’ post-qualified experience (<abbr title=\"Post Qualification Experience\">PQE</abbr>), around £50,000 (dependent on location and experience)</li>\n  <li>Lawyer (Grade 7) - generally equivalent to 3 or more years’ <abbr title=\"Post Qualification Experience\">PQE</abbr>, around £60,000 (dependent on location and experience)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"pensions\">Pensions</h2>\n\n<p>As civil servants, lawyers are eligible to join the civil service pension arrangements.</p>\n\n<p>Civil Service pensions are part of the overall pay and rewards package.</p>\n\n<p>Members contribute toward their pension and their employing departments also pay a significant contribution to their pension.</p>\n\n<p>The pension scheme is set by statute and is managed by the Cabinet Office. It’s supported by a governance group of representatives nominated by Cabinet Office and the Council of Civil Service Unions.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"government-legal-training-programme\">Government Legal Training Programme</h2>\n\n<p>A training programme is available to government lawyers which includes a wide range of topics such as:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>International Trade law</li>\n  <li>Constitutional, Administrative and Information law</li>\n  <li>Commercial law</li>\n  <li>Employment law</li>\n  <li>Litigation</li>\n  <li>Legislation</li>\n  <li>Personal Effectiveness and Leadership</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The training programme has been created by government lawyers. It concentrates on the specialist legal issues and broader skills essential to provide the government with a responsive and adaptable legal service.</p>\n\n<p>Lawyers who are new to the Civil Service are required to attend a 2 day induction course  which provides an insight into all aspects of government legal practice.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"civil-service-code\">Civil Service Code</h2>\n\n<p>As civil servants, lawyers will be appointed on merit on the basis of fair and open competition.</p>\n\n<p>Lawyers will be expected to carry out their role with dedication and a commitment to the Civil Service and its core values: integrity, honesty, objectivity and impartiality:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>‘integrity’ is putting the obligations of public service above your own personal interests</li>\n  <li>‘honesty’ is being truthful and open</li>\n  <li>‘objectivity’ is basing your advice and decisions on rigorous analysis of the evidence</li>\n  <li>‘impartiality’ is acting solely according to the merits of the case and serving equally well governments of different political persuasions</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/civil-service-code/the-civil-service-code\">The core values are set out in the Civil Service Code.</a></p>\n\n</div>" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
